**Lemma D.4**.: _Let \(\mathbf{A}\in\mathbb{R}^{d\times d}\) be a positive definite matrix and \(\mathbf{u}\in\mathbb{R}^{d}\) be such that \(\left\|\mathbf{u}\right\|_{A^{-1}}^{2}>d\). For \(c:=d/\ell\in(0,1)\) we have \(\nu_{d}(\mathbf{u})\leq\sqrt{c\cdot e^{1-c}}\), where \(\nu_{d}\) is defined as in (21). In particular, if \(\left\|\mathbf{u}\right\|_{A^{-1}}^{2}>d\), then \(\nu_{d}(\mathbf{u})\leq\nicefrac{{q\sqrt{c}}}{{\sqrt{c}}}\)._

